window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>First, businesses discovered quality as a key competitive edge; next came science. Now, Donald A. Norman, former Director of the Institute for Cognitive Science at the University of California, reveals how smart design is the new frontier. <i>The Design of Everyday Things</i> is a powerful primer on how - and why - some products satisfy customers while others only frustrate them. </p>"; 
